Here's the corrected function to draw a poker table:

```javascript
function drawTable(svgEl) {
  // Define dimensions as variables
  const bounding = svgEl.getBoundingClientRect();
  const width = bounding.width;
  const height = bounding.height;

  // Create the path element and set its attributes
  const path = document.createElementNS("http://www.w3.org/2000/svg", "path");

  // Define capsule shape using relative units based on width and height
  let d = `M${width * 0.05} ${height * 0.3} `;
  d += `Q${width * 0.05} ${height * 0.1}, ${width * 0.2} ${height * 0.1} `;
  d += `H${width * 0.8} `;
  d += `Q${width * 0.95} ${height * 0.1}, ${width * 0.95} ${height * 0.3} `;
  d += `Q${width} ${(50 / 60) * height}, ${width / 2} ${(180 / 600) * height} `;
  d += `Q${5} ${(50 / 60) * height}, ${5} ${(30 / 60) * height} Z`;

  path.setAttribute("d", d);
  path.style.stroke = "#000";
  path.style.fill = "#0c0";
  path.style.strokeWidth = "1em";

  // Append the path element to the parent SVG
  svgEl.appendChild(path);
}
```

In the corrected function, I have fixed the variable names and ensured proper usage of JavaScript template literals when defining the path. Additionally, I have modified the path definition to use relative width and height values to create a more flexible shape. This will allow the poker table to adapt to different sizes of the parent SVG element.
